   * 			 {(1 - \nu \sin^2\theta)
   * 			  \sqrt{1 - k^2 \sin^2\theta}}
   * @f]
   * For  @f$ \phi= \pi/2 @f$ this becomes the complete elliptic integral of
   * the third kind, @f$ \Pi(k,\nu) @f$.  @see comp_ellint_3.
